## 4. Updated Tools and Approach

I am not changing the core toolset for P02. I will continue using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, JSON, and localStorage because they match the project scope and keep the system simple and maintainable.

The most effective part of my workflow during P01 was separating planning from implementation. I used ChatGPT to work through logic, structure, and design decisions, and then used Cursor to implement and modify the code. This allowed me to move quickly while still understanding what I was building.

For testing, I used Live Server to preview changes in real time, which helped catch issues before deployment. For deployment, I used GitHub Pages, which provided a simple pipeline to push changes and verify them live.

If I were starting over, I would have conducted a more thourough investigation, define the data model more completely from the beginning. I initially assumed rank-based requirements were sufficient, but real use showed that age must also be included. Addressing that earlier would have prevented rework in this phase.   